Module lanat

Class Argument.PrefixChar

java.lang.Object
lanat.Argument.PrefixChar
Enclosing class:
Argument<Type extends ArgumentType<TInner>,TInner>
public static class Argument.PrefixChar extends Object
The list of prefixes that can be used.

The AUTO prefix will be automatically set depending on the Operating System.

  • Method Details

    • fromCharUnsafe

      @NotNull public static @NotNull Argument.PrefixChar fromCharUnsafe(char character)
      Creates a new PrefixChar with the specified non-whitespace character.

      NOTE:
       The constant fields of this class should be used instead of this method. Other characters could break compatibility with shells using special characters as prefixes, such as the | or ; characters.

      Parameters:
      character - the character that will be used as a prefix
